{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"base-doggish-barracuda","description":"## Context\nAn inbound external user with no local mapping mints a placeholder identity storing the raw `(provider, external_id, display_name)` that idempotently upgrades when a real mapping appears (Gitea OriginalAuthorID discipline).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] An unmapped inbound Jira user creates a placeholder identity storing (provider, external_id, display_name).\n- [ ] Re-running resolution after a real mapping is added upgrades the placeholder idempotently — test asserts one identity, not two.\n- [ ] The mapping key is the provider's stable id so the upgrade is provider-neutral.","id":"2f13-0648-0e41-474d","parent_id":"e68d-b701-4dd9-47aa","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"identity: inbound ghost/placeholder + idempotent auto-upgrade"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783735876702294001,"uuid":"82f38938-1f65-4c76-98a0-fca8690d2b09"}